<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Fortunado</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-01 15:55:28</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Actually, the last post is wrong!<BR>
<BR>
For starters, the Cloak of Flames is 30% haste, not 40%, so stop dreaming. Second, the Runed Bolster Belt is slightly less than this, in the 25-30% range, nearly as equal.<BR>
<BR>
The Seblisian Berserker Cloak is also 30% haste, on top of which, it is not dropped off a supreme mob akin to Nagafen, but rather a simple named in Sebilis.<BR>
<BR>
Comparing the Berserker Cloak to Cloak of Flames:<BR>
+9 dex bonus: equal<BR>
+9 agi bonus: equal<BR>
+50 hp bonus: equal<BR>
+30% haste:   equal<BR>
<BR>
Where do they differ?<BR>
<BR>
Cloak of Flames has +1 ac and +15 fire resist over the Berserker Cloak, while Berserker Cloak has +9 str and +9 stamina over CoF. It does not take a rocket scientist to realize that the Berserker Cloak is so much better. With that 9 strength and 9 stamina comes an increase in attack power, average damage, maximum damage per swing, and additional hit points and damage absorption from the stamina, all for the sacrifice of ONE armor class and resistance to fire that can easily be acquired elsewhere.<BR>
<BR>
Now, why does this cloak exist? First of all, I have spent every waking day since the inception of Kunark in Sebilis. It is the only dungeon I am familiar with, far more knowledgeable of than the average player, but at the expense of knowing jack about the rest of the continent. The treasures in this dungeon are phenomenal, but the average mob is a level 50 froglok. You thought the Ghoul Lord was tough in his day, the Krup and Ilis frogloks will walk all over you (they even summon, warp to you, gate away if in danger) and they pale in comparison to some of the deeper mobs like Myconids, Reet frogloks, etc.<BR>
<BR>
There are two mobs in Sebilis that drop these cloaks, that is: Berserker Cloak and Heirophant Cloak. The original Heirophant Cloak was a mock-up of the White Dragonscale Cloak (now it's even better as it received a boost in stats last patch). These two cloaks are nothing more than rewards to those people who brave the depths of Sebilis but have never had the luck to win a dragon cloak from Nagafen or Vox. Just because back in the day, pre-Kunark, the CoF and White Dragon Cloak were such remarkable items, does not mean they continue to be so in Expansion. Every patch, people blindly rush back to the dragons for more chances at these cloaks, and people like me just laugh at you from the depths of Sebilis as we get the same kinds of items (arguably better) on a daily basis. There is also a belt in this dungeon which is a combination of the Runed Bolster Belt and Bone Clasp Girdle (two dragon belts), but that's for another post :)<BR>
<BR>
Chow for now!<BR>
<BR>
Fortunado</font></td></tr></table>
